{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UkJENPmcT9jJ2rPCYVdJZT","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Kaggle Kernels\n2\t\n3\tUse this workflow to fetch, browse, and research Kaggle competition kernels/notebooks.\n4\t\n5\t## Inputs\n6\t\n7\t| Input | Required | Description |\n8\t|---|---|---|\n9\t| `competition_id` | Yes for ingest/query/research | Kaggle competition slug. |\n10\t| `kernel_ref` | Yes for read | Kaggle kernel reference such as `owner/kernel-slug` or a Kaggle code URL. |\n11\t| `KAGGLE_API_TOKEN` | Yes | KGAT token string for Kaggle APIs and SDK search. |\n12\t| Optional filters | No | Search, author, vote threshold, sorting, limits, raw output, and refresh flags. |\n13\t\n14\t## Core Commands\n15\t\n16\t```bash\n17\tpython ./scripts/kernel_ingest.py <competition_id> [--max-pages N] [--sort-by FIELD] [--page-size N]\n18\tpython ./scripts/kernel_query.py <competition_id> [--search TERM] [--min-votes N] [--author NAME] [--limit N] [--as-json]\n19\tpython ./scripts/kernel_read.py <kernel_ref> [--competition-id ID] [--raw] [--force]\n20\tpython ./scripts/kernel_db_info.py [competition_id]\n21\t```\n22\t\n23\tSort options for ingest are `hotness`, `dateCreated`, `dateRun`, and `voteCount`.\n24\t\n25\t## Top Kernel And Lineage Research\n26\t\n27\tUse this when the user asks for top kernels, leaderboard notebook research, public score verification, or how public notebooks build on each other.\n28\t\n29\tProgress checklist:\n30\t\n31\t```text\n32\t- [ ] Phase 1: Collect leaderboard and kernel lists\n33\t- [ ] Phase 2: Pull kernel metadata and code for top kernels\n34\t- [ ] Phase 3: Build dependency graph from metadata and code refs\n35\t- [ ] Phase 4: Write report\n36\t```\n37\t\n38\tFetch public kernel scores:\n39\t\n40\t```bash\n41\tpython ./scripts/fetch_top_kernel_scores.py <competition_id> --sort descending\n42\tpython ./scripts/fetch_top_kernel_scores.py <competition_id> --sort ascending\n43\tpython ./scripts/fetch_kernel_score.py <owner/kernel-slug>\n44\t```\n45\t\n46\tThe top-score script first enumerates competition-scoped kernels through the Kaggle API, then enriches exact `owner/slug` refs with SDK score data. Do not use broad SDK search results as the source of truth for which kernels belong to a competition.\n47\t\n48\tCollect leaderboard and source evidence:\n49\t\n50\t```bash\n51\tkaggle kernels list --competition <competition_id> --sort-by voteCount --page-size 40 -v\n52\tkaggle competitions leaderboard <competition_id> --show -v\n53\tmkdir -p /tmp/kernel_research/<short-name>\n54\tcd /tmp/kernel_research/<short-name>\n55\tkaggle kernels pull <owner/slug> -m\n56\t```\n57\t\n58\tExtract evidence from `kernel-metadata.json` (`kernel_sources`, `dataset_sources`) and notebook/script source (Kaggle URLs, credit strings, `/kaggle/input/` references, author mentions).\n59\t\n60\tWrite `top_kernels_research.md` unless the user requests another path. Include leaderboard snapshot, verified public scores, lineage chains with `[metadata]` or `[code ref]` labels, observed techniques, open questions, and links.\n61\t\n62\t## Storage\n63\t\n64\t| Path | Contents |\n65\t|---|---|\n66\t| `data/kernels.db` | SQLite kernel metadata and competition info |\n67\t| `data/notebooks/<comp>/<ref>/` | Cached notebooks and `kernel-metadata.json` |\n68\t| `top_kernels_research.md` | Optional top-kernel and lineage report |\n69\t| `/tmp/kernel_research/<short-name>` | Temporary pulled kernel evidence |\n70\t\n71\t## Workflow-Specific Troubleshooting\n72\t\n73\tSee [SKILL.md](SKILL.md#troubleshooting) for common credential, access, cache, and rate-limit failures.\n74\t\n75\t| Symptom | Action |\n76\t|---|---|\n77\t| SDK score search omits a score | Keep the kernel row and label the score as missing. |\n78\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc87655d-e6ca-4a83-a259-05b02b16b06f","uuid":"57154edc-f8ac-4bdd-a109-2120f19794ef","timestamp":"2026-06-13T15:04:21.518Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/nvidia-kaggle/.claude/skills/nvidia-kaggle-skill/kernels.md","content":"# Kaggle Kernels\n\nUse this workflow to fetch, browse, and research Kaggle competition kernels/notebooks.\n\n## Inputs\n\n| Input | Required | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `competition_id` | Yes for ingest/query/research | Kaggle competition slug. |\n| `kernel_ref` | Yes for read | Kaggle kernel reference such as `owner/kernel-slug` or a Kaggle code URL. |\n| `KAGGLE_API_TOKEN` | Yes | KGAT token string for Kaggle APIs and SDK search. |\n| Optional filters | No | Search, author, vote threshold, sorting, limits, raw output, and refresh flags. |\n\n## Core Commands\n\n```bash\npython ./scripts/kernel_ingest.py <competition_id> [--max-pages N] [--sort-by FIELD] [--page-size N]\npython ./scripts/kernel_query.py <competition_id> [--search TERM] [--min-votes N] [--author NAME] [--limit N] [--as-json]\npython ./scripts/kernel_read.py <kernel_ref> [--competition-id ID] [--raw] [--force]\npython ./scripts/kernel_db_info.py [competition_id]\n```\n\nSort options for ingest are `hotness`, `dateCreated`, `dateRun`, and `voteCount`.\n\n## Top Kernel And Lineage Research\n\nUse this when the user asks for top kernels, leaderboard notebook research, public score verification, or how public notebooks build on each other.\n\nProgress checklist:\n\n```text\n- [ ] Phase 1: Collect leaderboard and kernel lists\n- [ ] Phase 2: Pull kernel metadata and code for top kernels\n- [ ] Phase 3: Build dependency graph from metadata and code refs\n- [ ] Phase 4: Write report\n```\n\nFetch public kernel scores:\n\n```bash\npython ./scripts/fetch_top_kernel_scores.py <competition_id> --sort descending\npython ./scripts/fetch_top_kernel_scores.py <competition_id> --sort ascending\npython ./scripts/fetch_kernel_score.py <owner/kernel-slug>\n```\n\nThe top-score script first enumerates competition-scoped kernels through the Kaggle API, then enriches exact `owner/slug` refs with SDK score data. Do 